ng OgnlRuntime. However, it might not be necessary for standard public bean usage. Still, achieving meaningful coverage with reflective access for metadata seems important. I think running a dependency graph for the artifact could clarify things, but existing tests seem to include the required JVM arguments already. It's intricate!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating library setup requirements**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the library needs additional setup beyond the typical test scaffold to achieve meaningful coverage. The current build already includes some parameters, but it's not deterministic. Also, a fix may need awareness that JDK 25 has removed the SecurityManager, meaning tests requiring System.setSecurityManager might fail unless they're guarded. In fact, existing tests attempting to set the security manager will fail since JDK 24 and 25 permanently disallow it. I'll need to consider these factors carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering security manager settings**\\n\\nI'm wondering if setting the system property `java.security.manager=allow` could be beneficial, but it's clear that this won't work in JDK 25. So, it seems like this isn't actually part of the setup. Instead, I might focus on an advisory preparation that includes guidance on using add-opens and avoiding or forcing a disable on the security manager. I’m just pondering if that approach might be seen as overreaching. It’s a complex situation!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL is a pure-Java expression/reflection library and its only runtime dependency, Javassist, is declared transitively, but its own JDK 17+ test profile requires module-opening JVM arguments for reflective coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Run generated JVM tests with module opens matching OGNL's upstream JDK 17+ test profile: `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`. If tests exercise OGNL's optional JDK 9+ accessible-object handler, set `ognl.UseJDK9PlusAccessHandler=true` before `OgnlRuntime` initializes. Avoid depending on `System.setSecurityManager`/`ognl.security.manager` behavior for JDK 25 coverage; prefer tests that cover normal expression parsing/evaluation, property/method access, map/list/array navigation, constructors/static access, and Javassist-backed expression compilation.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"SecurityManager-related OGNL paths are JDK-version-sensitive and may fail on JDK 25 regardless of metadata quality.\",\n    \"The `org.javassist:javassist:3.29.0-GA` dependency is already transitive from `ognl:ognl:3.3.5`; adding it explicitly should not be necessary unless local Gradle resolution proves otherwise.\",\n    \"Native Image and local Gradle runs remain authoritative for whether the module opens are sufficient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08317051a046a467016a411eca8c608194be6bede0e910d2a2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 698, "output": 1372, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41494, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782652603235, "responseId": "resp_08317051a046a467016a411ebbb6648194bcadad8edc335631"}, "toolResults": []}
